          <text><![CDATA[<p><strong>21st Century Investment Act of 201</strong><b>7</b></p> <p>This bill amends the Internal Revenue Code to: (1) modify the tax credit for increasing research activities to allow an increased 25% tax credit rate for expenses for research, substantially all of which occurs in the United States; and (2) increase to 15%, through 2024, the tax deduction for income attributable to domestic manufacturing production activities for which substantially all of the research and development occurred in the United States. </p>]]></text>
          <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
